fields.name: Elm Bonsai
fields.description: This Elm bonsai in blue pot is from 1982 and is a easy to maintain inside bonsai. the leaves will change to a soft orange during the fall and will then fall off. no worries this tree will sprout new leaves in april.
fields.image: Afbeelding van Ilona Ilyés via Pixabay 2.jpg

fields.name: Blue Spruce
fields.description: This Blue spruce is a perfect tree to make as a focal point in your garden or balcony. it requires almost no work and will stay green year round.
fields.image: Afbeelding van Ilona Ilyés via Pixabay4.jpg

fields.name: Bonsai pruning scissors
fields.description: These prunning scissors are made to cut small leaves and branches.

fields.name: Azeale Bonsai
fields.description: This Bonsai stays green most of the year and in the summer this will bloom with bright red flowers all over the bonsai.  This is a very good centrepiece for your garden.

fields.name: Cedar lebani
fields.description: This Mediterranean tree stays green year-round and therefore will brighten your garden year-round. this bonsai is very easy to maintain and is a great bonsai for people to get into bonsai.

fields.name: Flowering tree
fields.description: Even though this bonsai will bloom for a short period in august it does so beautifully. This bonsai is green the rest of the year.

fields.name: Pliers
fields.description: These pliers are used to cut bigger branches and roots of bonsai.

fields.name: scissors
fields.description: these scissors are to cut smaller branches and leaves.

fields.name: Red maple
fields.description: This slow-growing tree is mostly known for its deep red leaves in fall. during spring and summer, the leaves are green. this is certain to give your garden a nice colour.

fields.name: Podocarpus
fields.description: this is a conifer out japan and china is strong and therefore easy to use as a bonsai. this tree is able to survive inside and outside.

fields.name: ficus ginseng
fields.description: This is the most common tree used for bonsai due to its strong trunk and the leaves that stay on the tree year-round.

fields.name: Small Elm forest bonsai
fields.description: This bonsai Forrest consist out of multiple smaller bonsai. this tree gives the feeling you are in the middle of the forest while still indoor.

fields.name: American pineleaf
fields.description: This bonsai looks like a pine but however, this leafy tree is certainly not a pine. this bonsai will lose its leaves in later fall and have green leaves from the spring.

fields.name: pine
fields.description: This older pine was made later in life and a lot of the tree died of . the branches that still contained life were redirected and that gives us this beautiful bonsai.

fields.name: fiscus ginseng rock
fields.description: This bonsai was grown on a small patch of rocks with a little amount of earth. its beautiful composition is created by running the roots over the stones and growing some moss over that.

fields.name: pine forest bonsai
fields.description: this beautiful bonsai forest consists of pine trees planted on rocky hills. the scrubs are a mix of ferns, moss, and small blooming flowers. this 30-year-old bonsai is sure to amaze everybody that comes to visit your house or office.

fields.name: spruce bonsai
fields.description: This spruce bonsai will be a focal point of your garden.

fields.name: Arbutus menziesii
fields.description: This bonsai will give small red berries during spring into summer. these berries are not edible however they do give a nice colour to the tree. this tree will hold leaves year-round.

fields.name: American oak
fields.description: This sturdy slow-growing bonsai is 60 years old and will change its colour leaves from light green in spring to dark green in summer to yellow and ending in orange in the fall. This colourful bonsai is sure to impress anybody with your garden.

fields.name: pinus cembra
fields.description: This alpine pine is normally known for its pine seeds that are edible however, it makes for a beautiful bonsai as well. This bonsai is 20 years old and will grow for many more years to come. It is easy to maintain it only needs water every week and enough sunlight.

fields.name: pine seeds- pinus cembra
fields.description: these alpine pine seeds are of the famous pine nuts tree. They are slow-growing and will not produce pine seeds for the first 30 years but they make for beautiful bonsai trees if formed properly.

fields.name: spruce seeds
fields.description: spruce is family of the conifer family. this will grow with soft green needles and is very easy to bend and shape.

fields.name: Elm seeds
fields.description: these elm seeds will grow in sturdy elm trees if given enough love and time.

fields.name: acer seeds
fields.description: the Acer is a well know 5 point star leaf it comes in multiple colours however these ones will have red-green leaves.

fields.name: Pine small bonsai
fields.description: You will always be able to find a nice spot for this small bonsai. it will stay green year-round and can be grown to become much larger if wanted.

fields.name: conifer bonsai
fields.description: This bonsai might not be the oldest but it is grown on a beautiful composition of rock and moss and gives a feeling of rough nature.

fields.name: large spruce bonsai
fields.description: this large spruce bonsai is 80 years old and still going strong. this bonsai has a height of 50cm and will stay green year-round.

fields.name: small round pot
fields.description: this small round pot is a good pot for smaller bonsai.  It has a hole on the bottom for drainage and a dish to capture the excess water.  shouldn't be left outside in winter.

fields.name: bonsai pot
fields.description: This pot is for inside bonsai. It can be placed outside during spring, summer and fall but will break if it freezes. This pot is for small bonsai after the bonsai grows over 20 above the pot the bonsai should be placed in a bigger pot.

fields.name: ficus ginseng small
fields.description:
This bonsai is still quite small and young. however, it is already quite beautiful!
it is low maintenance for it only requires some water every week. this is the perfect tree for beginners in bonsai.

fields.name: wire Big
fields.description: big wire for binding the bonsai in the desired shape. wrap it around the thicker parts that you want to shape at a 45-degree angle and then bend the wire so the branches will bend and harden in the correct way.

fields.name: wire medium
fields.description: medium wire for binding the bonsai in the desired shape. wrap it around the medium parts that you want to shape at a 45-degree angle and then bend the wire so the branches will bend and harden in the correct way.

fields.name: wire small
fields.description: small wire for binding the bonsai in the desired shape. wrap it around the smaller parts that you want to shape at a 45-degree angle and then bend the wire so the branches will bend and harden in the correct way.
